14:38.573 --> 14:40.836
HEY, THAT'S MY BOARD!

14:43.317 --> 14:44.579
I DON'T KNOW YOU.

14:44.709 --> 14:46.102
OFF OUR WAVES
OR WE'LL DROWN YOU.

14:46.233 --> 14:47.799
HEY, I'M NOT DONE SURFING YET.

14:47.930 --> 14:49.149
LOOK, WE DON'T WANT ANY TROUBLE.

14:49.279 --> 14:50.367
ALL I WANT IS MY SURFBOARD BACK.

14:50.498 --> 14:52.326
FINDER'S KEEPERS.

14:52.456 --> 14:53.501
YOURS, TOO.

15:17.090 --> 15:19.396
[BEEPING]

15:20.484 --> 15:23.009
KMF295 FROM BAYWATCH RESCUE 1

15:23.139 --> 15:25.359
RECEIVING EMERGENCY TRANSMISSION
FROM MATT BRODY.

15:25.489 --> 15:28.362
RESPONDING CODE 3.
REQUEST IMMEDIATE BACKUP.

15:32.453 --> 15:34.281
BAYWATCH

15:55.084 --> 15:56.694
LIFEGUARD

15:59.828 --> 16:01.221
COME ON, GUYS! LET'S BOOK IT!

16:01.351 --> 16:02.526
LET'S JETTISON!

16:03.832 --> 16:06.008
YOU'RE GOING BELLY UP, MAN!

17:38.579 --> 17:40.798
YOU KNOW, HAVE TO KEEP THIS ON
TILL IT WEARS OUT AND FALLS OFF.

17:40.929 --> 17:43.323
JUST MAKE SURE YOU DON'T CUT OFF
MY CIRCULATION.

17:45.455 --> 17:47.153
WELL,
ACCORDING TO A LOT OF WOMEN

17:47.283 --> 17:50.112
I'VE MET ON THE BEACH,
I ALREADY HAVE.

17:50.243 --> 17:52.549
AND THEY'RE NOT AT ALL HAPPY
ABOUT IT.

17:55.422 --> 17:56.205
WHAT CAN I SAY?

17:56.336 --> 17:57.380
WHAT CAN I SAY?

17:59.339 --> 18:00.905
YOU DON'T HAVE TO SAY ANYTHING.

18:11.351 --> 18:13.222
-WHAT ARE YOU THINKING ABOUT?
-I'M NOT.

18:13.353 --> 18:14.658
I'M NOT THINKING.

18:16.007 --> 18:17.531
WHAT WOULD YOU BE THINKING
IF YOU WERE?

18:21.143 --> 18:22.536
I'D BE THINKING...

18:24.842 --> 18:26.844
THAT THIS WHOLE THING
HAS GOTTA BE CRAZY

18:26.975 --> 18:31.110
'CAUSE THE INK ON
MY DIVORCE PAPERS IS BARELY DRY.

18:34.896 --> 18:36.724
IS THIS A RICOCHET ROMANCE?

18:38.291 --> 18:40.075
-DID I GET YOU ON THE REBOUND?
-NO.

18:42.033 --> 18:44.123
NO, YOU STOLE ME AT MID-COURT.

18:46.342 --> 18:47.604
I DID, HUH?

18:49.780 --> 18:51.913
WELL, WHAT AM I SUPPOSED TO DO
WITH YOU NOW?

18:52.696 --> 18:55.438
I DON'T KNOW.
DO SOME FANCY DRIBBLING

18:55.569 --> 18:56.961
AND SLAM DUNK.

18:57.571 --> 18:58.659
TO WIN THE GAME?

18:59.268 --> 19:00.356
NO.

19:01.009 --> 19:02.271
SEND IT INTO OVERTIME.

19:06.710 --> 19:08.059
SOUNDS EXCITING.

19:08.190 --> 19:10.236
WAIT TILL THE PLAYOFFS
THIS WEEKEND.

19:11.367 --> 19:12.281
OH?

19:13.326 --> 19:18.287
ONE ON ONE IN CATALINA.

19:20.681 --> 19:23.771
VIEW OF THE HARBOR,
BALCONY UNDER THE STARS.

19:24.902 --> 19:27.166
FIRST ONE TO SCORE 20 WINS.

19:29.342 --> 19:30.212
YOU'RE ON.

19:32.214 --> 19:33.346
WHAT ABOUT HOBIE?

19:33.476 --> 19:35.957
HE'LL BE WITH HIS MOM
TILL MONDAY.

19:40.004 --> 19:42.529
SO WHAT ABOUT A PRACTICE GAME
RIGHT NOW?

19:55.716 --> 19:57.761
OKAY, SUMMER. HERE YOU GO.

19:57.892 --> 19:59.502
-THANKS.
-SURE.

20:24.397 --> 20:25.833
SO THE ONE GUY
ALMOST DECAPITATES YOU

20:25.963 --> 20:27.487
WITH A SURFBOARD.
THEN WHAT HAPPENS?

20:27.617 --> 20:29.010
THEN WE GO AT IT.

20:29.140 --> 20:30.185
YOU'VE GOT THEIR DESCRIPTIONS.

20:30.316 --> 20:31.752
WHY DON'T YOU JUST BUST THEM?

20:31.882 --> 20:33.797
IT'S ONLY ASSAULT
IF THEY INITIATED THE FIGHT.

20:33.928 --> 20:35.234
WE DIDN'T START IT.

20:36.278 --> 20:37.236
WHO THREW THE FIRST PUNCH?

20:38.541 --> 20:40.021
WELL, I GUESS I DID.

20:40.151 --> 20:41.544
YOU KNOW, IT'S LIKE
IF A BIG WAVE IS COMING

20:41.675 --> 20:42.937
AND YOU WANT TO GET IT
BEFORE IT GETS YOU.

20:43.067 --> 20:45.156
GARDNER,
OBVIOUSLY IT WAS SELF-DEFENSE.

20:45.287 --> 20:46.854
I'M SURE IT WAS,
BUT THE DISTRICT ATTORNEY

20:46.984 --> 20:48.334
IS GOING TO ASK
THAT SAME QUESTION.

20:48.464 --> 20:50.423
HEY, THERE'S A LOT OF RISK
IN THE OCEAN.

20:50.553 --> 20:52.120
IF IT'S NOT THESE SHOOTERS,
THEN IT'S SOMETHING ELSE.

20:52.251 --> 20:53.208
IT DOESN'T REALLY MATTER.

20:54.340 --> 20:55.471
I'M OUT OF HERE. LATER, MAN.

20:56.646 --> 20:58.257
SLADE,
I'M GOING TO NEED A PHONE NUMBER

20:58.387 --> 21:00.041
AND AN ADDRESS
WHERE I CAN REACH YOU.

21:00.171 --> 21:04.350
NO PHONE.
THE ADDRESS IS 853 D-T-S.

21:04.480 --> 21:06.439
-IS THAT A STREET?
-LICENSE PLATE.

21:08.005 --> 21:10.094
DON'T WORRY.

21:10.225 --> 21:12.053
YOU'LL BE ABLE TO FIND THEM
WHEREVER THE SURF IS HAPPENING.

21:22.498 --> 21:24.544
YOU SHOULD PULL IN THE TUBE
OR YOU'RE GONNA GET WORKED.

21:24.674 --> 21:26.502
UM, HI.

21:26.633 --> 21:28.852
YEAH, I JUST KIND OF ALWAYS
WANTED TO LEARN HOW TO SURF.

21:29.418 --> 21:30.985
MAYBE YOU SHOULD TRY IT
IN THE WATER SOMETIME.

21:33.204 --> 21:34.641
OH, THIS IS YOURS?

21:34.771 --> 21:36.730
I'M SORRY. I HOPE
I DIDN'T DO ANYTHING TO IT.

21:36.860 --> 21:38.645
THAT WAS A PRETTY HEAVY WIPEOUT,

21:38.775 --> 21:40.429
BUT IT LOOKS LIKE
IT'S GOING TO BE OKAY.

21:40.560 --> 21:42.126
YOU A LIFEGUARD?

21:42.257 --> 21:43.824
WELL, I JUST MADE IT
THROUGH THE QUALIFYING SWIM,

21:43.954 --> 21:45.826
BUT ROOKIE SCHOOL DOESN'T START
FOR ANOTHER WEEK.

21:46.522 --> 21:47.523
MY NAME'S SUMMER.

21:48.307 --> 21:49.830
OH?
THE ULTIMATE CALIFORNIA GIRL?

21:49.960 --> 21:51.614
YEAH, I WISH.

21:51.745 --> 21:53.312
ME AND MY MOM JUST MOVED OUT
HERE FROM PITTSBURGH.

21:53.877 --> 21:55.575
-WHAT'S YOUR NAME?
-SLADE.

21:56.489 --> 21:57.707
THAT'S IT? JUST SLADE?

21:58.621 --> 21:59.840
JIMMY.

21:59.970 --> 22:01.189
IT'S NICE TO MEET YOU, SUMMER.

22:01.320 --> 22:02.756
JIMMY?

22:03.409 --> 22:04.279
SLADE.

22:06.150 --> 22:08.109
MAYBE YOU COULD TEACH ME
HOW TO SURF SOMETIME.

22:09.719 --> 22:11.286
SOUNDS LIKE A PLAN.

22:12.679 --> 22:14.724
LOOK, I UNDERSTAND ALL THAT,

22:14.855 --> 22:16.552
BUT THIS ISN'T JUST PERSONAL.

22:17.466 --> 22:18.728
IF WE CAN'T WORK TOGETHER,

22:18.859 --> 22:20.600
WE CAN DISRUPT
THE ENTIRE HEADQUARTERS.

22:21.427 --> 22:23.646
DON, YOU'RE THE CHIEF NOW.

22:23.777 --> 22:25.344
YOU CAN ASSIGN ANYBODY
ANYWHERE YOU WANT.

22:25.474 --> 22:27.346
NOW, I'M TELLING YOU,
IT'S HER OR ME.

22:27.476 --> 22:28.521
[KNOCKING]

22:28.651 --> 22:30.044
YEAH, I'LL BE RIGHT THERE.

22:30.174 --> 22:31.001
LOOK,
THERE'S SOMEONE AT THE DOOR.

22:31.132 --> 22:32.568
I GOTTA GO.

22:32.699 --> 22:33.917
BALL'S IN YOUR COURT.
YOU KNOW HOW I FEEL.

22:36.137 --> 22:37.834
-YEAH?
-HI.

22:38.748 --> 22:39.749
CAN I COME IN?

22:40.881 --> 22:41.838
SURE.

22:53.241 --> 22:54.808
SO, HOW'S HOBIE?

22:54.938 --> 22:56.070
I'D LOVE TO SEE HIM.

22:57.506 --> 22:59.595
HE CAUGHT A SUMMER COLD.
HE'S SLEEPING.

23:04.121 --> 23:05.993
SO, ARE YOU DATING ANYBODY
IN PARTICULAR?

23:06.689 --> 23:07.951
WHY ARE YOU HERE?

23:09.213 --> 23:10.389
WHY AM I HERE?

23:12.086 --> 23:13.870
I'M HERE BECAUSE...

23:14.697 --> 23:16.090
BECAUSE I KNOW IT MUST BE HARD

23:16.220 --> 23:17.221
TO HAVE SOMEONE
YOU PRACTICALLY TRAINED

23:17.352 --> 23:18.484
WIND UP AS YOUR BOSS.

23:19.310 --> 23:20.921
YOU'RE NOT MY BOSS.

23:21.051 --> 23:22.836
YOU'RE RESPONSIBLE
FOR HEADQUARTERS.

23:22.966 --> 23:24.272
I'M RESPONSIBLE FOR THE BEACH.

23:24.403 --> 23:26.143
THAT IS NOT ENTIRELY ACCURATE.

23:26.970 --> 23:29.146
BUT THE POINT IS IS THAT I'VE
INVESTED TOO MUCH OF MY CAREER

23:29.277 --> 23:30.974
TO WALK AWAY FROM THIS JOB.

23:31.105 --> 23:33.412
THOUGHT THAT WAS YOUR STYLE.
"WALK AWAY."

23:36.937 --> 23:38.068
I'M SORRY, MITCH.

23:38.199 --> 23:39.505
I KNOW THAT I HURT YOU,

23:39.635 --> 23:40.593
BUT BELIEVE ME,
IT WAS THE ONLY WAY.

23:40.723 --> 23:41.898
NO,
THERE ARE A LOT OF OTHER WAYS

23:42.029 --> 23:43.334
TO END A RELATIONSHIP

23:43.465 --> 23:44.466
BESIDES SHOVING A NOTE
UNDER A DOOR.

23:44.597 --> 23:46.337
I DIDN'T WANT IT TO END.

23:46.468 --> 23:47.556
THEN WHY THE HELL WOULD YOU
LEAVE ME AT THE FERRY?

23:47.687 --> 23:49.210
IT COULDN'T HAVE WORKED, MITCH.

23:49.906 --> 23:51.778
I DID WHAT WAS BEST
FOR BOTH OF US.

23:53.867 --> 23:56.130
OH, WHAT DIFFERENCE
DOES IT MAKE ANYWAY, HUH?

23:56.609 --> 23:57.871
IT'S WATER UNDER THE BRIDGE.

23:59.350 --> 24:01.527
MITCH, HOW LONG DID YOU WEAR
THAT BRACELET AFTER I LEFT?

24:04.965 --> 24:05.835
WHAT BRACELET?

24:07.358 --> 24:08.708
THE ONE I TIED ON YOUR WRIST.

24:10.144 --> 24:11.319
OH, YEAH, THAT BRACELET!

24:11.450 --> 24:13.669
I CUT IF OFF
AND THREW IT AWAY THE NEXT DAY.

24:14.714 --> 24:16.193
-YOU CUT IT OFF?
-YEAH. SNIP.

24:21.329 --> 24:23.157
I FOUND IT IN YOUR DESK DRAWER.

24:24.071 --> 24:25.855
WHAT THE HELL ARE YOU DOING
GOING THROUGH MY DESK?

24:25.986 --> 24:27.814
IT'S NOT CUT, MITCH.
IT'S WORN THROUGH.

24:27.944 --> 24:29.990
SO I SNAGGED IT ON SOME ROCKS
WHILE I WAS SCUBA DIVING.

24:30.120 --> 24:31.557
WHAT ARE YOU DOING
GOING THROUGH MY DESK?

24:31.687 --> 24:33.820
IT MEANS A LOT TO ME THAT
YOU'VE KEPT IT ALL THESE YEARS.

24:33.950 --> 24:36.779
I THREW IT AWAY
IN A JUNK DRAWER.

24:37.345 --> 24:38.955
IT'S A FRIENDSHIP BRACELET,
MITCH.

24:39.956 --> 24:41.262
CAN'T WE AT LEAST BE FRIENDS?

24:45.353 --> 24:46.920
LOOK, IT'S KIND OF LATE,
AND, UH...

24:50.489 --> 24:51.881
I DON'T WANT TO WAKE UP HOBIE.

24:56.103 --> 24:57.321
TELL HIM "HI" FOR ME.

25:21.911 --> 25:25.611
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

25:57.207 --> 26:02.561
♪ I THINK YOU MUST BE
PART OF ME ♪

26:03.866 --> 26:06.869
